  "steps": [
    {
      "name": "",
      "steps": [
        {
          "text": "Rinse the pork in cold water, cut into big chunks, put it into a pot, and cover it with 2 liters of water. Add salt, <Ingredient name=\"bay leaf\"  />, and cook until soft on medium heat, for about 30 minutes after the water starts to boil.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "While the pork is cooking, cut the ham and the sausages into 1/2 cm cubes.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "On a medium-sized skillet, heat olive oil on medium heat, cook the ham and the sausages for about 15 minutes, until brown on all sides.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "While the meats are cooking, prepare the vegetables.<br>\n**Tomatoes:** quarter and remove the roots.<br>\n**Onion:** peel and cut into small dice. **Garlic:** peel, and thinly slice. **Chile:** halve lengthwise, remove the root and seeds, and thinly slice.<br>\n**Olives:** thinly slice.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "When the pork is ready, let it cool, and remove it from the broth. Filter the broth using a metal sieve.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Blend the tomatoes using a blender.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Sauté the onion and chiles on a skillet with a bit of salt (add more olive oil if necessary), on medium heat, for about 2-3 minutes.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add the garlic to the onions and chiles, and keep cooking for 2-3 minutes more, until transparent.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add <Ingredient name=\"cumin seeds\"  />, and <Ingredient name=\"coriander seeds\"  />, and cook for another 30 seconds.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Transfer the pork, the ham and the sausages into the pot with the broth.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add the onion, chiles, garlic, and tomato sauce to the pot with the soup, and bring it to a boil.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add the olives and capers.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Reduce the heat to medium-low, and simmer the soup for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, then remove from the heat.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Add more salt if needed.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Prepare the vegetables for serving.<br>\n**Lime:** cut into 8 wedges. **Pickled cucumbers:** thinly slice.",
          "pause": false
        },
        {
          "text": "Serve: add into each plate of the soup two wedges of lime, 1/2 sliced pickled cucumber with a bit of its liquid, and a dollop of smetana.",
          "pause": false
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
